05/04/2006
PRAGUE, Czech Republic -- Prime Minister Jiri Paroubek reaffirmed his country's support for Macedonia's Euro-Atlantic integration bid during talks with Macedonian counterpart Vlado Buckovski in Prague on Tuesday (4 April).
Paroubek also praised Macedonia as a successful example of multiethnic co-existence and stability in the Balkans.
In other news Tuesday, the Macedonian Justice Ministry announced plans to raise funds from international donors in support of judicial reform.
The ministry has already contacted the resident representatives of donor organisations in Skopje.
(Macedonian Government Web site - 05/04/06;
Makfax - 04/04/06)
